{
  "texts": [
    "Significant improvements in both the Wolf Motor Function Test and Fugl-Meyer Assessment scores were reported for some patients in both clinical and home settings.",
    "The outcomes of AI algorithms were used in a variety of ways, primarily for prescribing individualized rehabilitation exercises to patients 27, [62] [63] [64], providing visualizations and feedback to patients in completing their exercises 27, [56] [57] [58] 62, 63, 66, and providing reports to clinicians about the progress of patients in their rehabilitation program 25, 27, [56] [57] [58] [59] [60] [61] [62] [63] [64] [65].",
    "Other uses of the outcomes of AI algorithms included attentiveness assessment of patients based on face and eye features 61 and pain assessment 27.",
    "The mediums to deliver feedback and visualizations to patients included desktop application 27, 57, 58, 61, [64] [65] [66], smartphone application 25, 60, 62, 63, web application 56, 59, 61, and wearable robot 27, 64.",
    "Research Question 2: How effective was the application of AI in the delivery of home-based VRehab programs for patients living in the community?."
  ]
}